history.content:
You should talk to your ESS adviser! Also, talk to the professor(s) for the classes that you would like to take for incomplete. If you explain your situation, the professors will most likely give you an incomplete for this semester. Hope you are doing better now!

That being said, you will have to complete all the missing work in the next semester so plan next semester's courses a little carefully because you will be doing this semester's work on the side as well.

children.subject: As long as you complete the coursework for it within the time frame the professors give you, I don't think it will affect the 2 techs per semester to graduate requirement. I definitely recommend talking to your ESS adviser. He/she will provide better guidance.

Especially since EECS has the requirement for taking two classes for letter grades per semester and would taking one incomplete this semester affect stuff next semester?
